				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Monocrystalline silicon solar cells, also known as mono-Si PV cells, are made from a single crystal of silicon. They are manufactured using the Czochralski method, where a 'seed' crystal of silicon is placed into a molten vat of pure silicon at a high temperature. This forms a single silicon crystal, called an ingot, that is sliced into thin silicon wafers which are then used in the solar panels. It is a form of photoelectric cell, whose electrical characteristics vary when exposed to light. They are often the electrical building blocks of photovoltaic modules, known as solar panels.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">单晶硅太阳能电池又称单晶硅光伏电池，由单晶硅晶体制成。单晶硅太阳能电池的制造方法是采用 Czochralski 法，即将硅的 &quot;种子 &quot;晶体放入高温的纯硅熔池中。这样就形成了称为硅锭的单晶硅晶体，再将其切成薄硅片，然后用于太阳能电池板。这是一种光电电池，其电气特性在光照下会发生变化。它们通常是被称为太阳能电池板的光电模块的电气构件。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Si</sumFormula>
